    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required level for Medium model risk. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 specifies a single standard load configuration as the regulatory reference and that all QoI comparisons satisfy the E/uval < 1.96 and <10% relative difference acceptance criteria across both laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
